      <title>Keeping upcase </title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ca_glossary/forum/general/keeping_upcase</link>
      <description>Hello,&#13;
&#13;
is there any solution to keep terms originally how were written in ezxmltext content? Currently all are in downcase. So for example if paragraph starts with:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;Lorem ipsum&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
it will be converted into&#13;
&lt;code&gt;lorem ipsum&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
I know it's possible to remove 'downcase' operator in ca_glossary.tpl, but it's not a solution for me. It will only use the way how term is written in glossary.&#13;
&#13;
Thanks</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Bartek Modzelewski)</author>
