    <item>
      <title>Re: Difference between Glossary operator and CA...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ca_glossary/forum/general/difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca_glossary/re_difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca3</link>
      <description>Hi,&#13;
&#13;
next improvement. If you want to use defined variants of a glossary word, e.g. "eZ", "eZ publish", "easy publish", use the following code:&#13;
&#13;
Add this line after line 107:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$variantsAttributeIdentifier = $ini-&gt;variable('GeneralSettings','VariantsAttributeIdentifier');&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
And add before the lines:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$matchArray[] = preg_quote( $title, '/' );&#13;
$tpl = templateInit();&#13;
...&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
the following code:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$variants = $dataMap[$variantsAttributeIdentifier]-&gt;content();&#13;
if (strlen($variants) &gt; 0) {&#13;
&#13;
$variants_arr = explode(",", $variants);&#13;
if (count($variants_arr) &gt; 0) {&#13;
&#13;
foreach ($variants_arr as &$itm) {
  $matchArray[] = preg_quote( $itm, '/' );&#13;
  $tpl = templateInit();&#13;
  $tpl-&gt;setVariable( 'title', $itm );&#13;
  $tpl-&gt;setVariable( 'glossaryUrl', $glossaryUrl );&#13;
  $tpl-&gt;setVariable( 'definition', $definition );&#13;
  $replaceArray[strtolower($itm)] = $tpl-&gt;fetch( 'design:ca_glossary.tpl' );&#13;
}&#13;
}&#13;
}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
You have to add a line in the glossary.ini.append.php for the variant attribute:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
# Glossar entry variants&#13;
VariantsAttributeIdentifier=variants&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
The values in the variant attribute are seperated by comma:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
eZ,eZ publish,easy publish&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Heiner Wurbs)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ca_glossary/forum/general/difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca_glossary/re_difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca3</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 15 Oct 2010 13:00:35 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Re: Difference between Glossary operator and CA...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ca_glossary/forum/general/difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca_glossary/re_difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca2</link>
      <description>Hi there,&#13;
&#13;
I have an improvement for this ca_glossary extension. If you want to use an ezxmltext for the Glossary word, then you could add the following code to autoloads/ca_glossary.php.&#13;
&#13;
Add after line 145:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$defObj = $dataMap[$definitionAttributeIdentifier];&#13;
if ($defObj-&gt;DataTypeString == "ezxmltext") {&#13;
    $XMLContent = $defObj-&gt;attribute( 'data_text' );&#13;
    $outputHandler = new eZXHTMLXMLOutput( $XMLContent, false, $defObj );&#13;
    $htmlContent =& $outputHandler->outputText();&#13;
    $definition = $htmlContent;&#13;
}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
Then you can use instead of a eztext as &#13;
DefinitionAttributeIdentifier=&#13;
an ezxmltext attribute.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Heiner Wurbs)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ca_glossary/forum/general/difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca_glossary/re_difference_between_glossary_operator_and_ca2</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 15 Oct 2010 10:36:59 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
